<h3 id="rules-for-python-variables">Rules for Python variables:</h3>

<ul>
  <li>A variable name must start with a letter or the underscore character.</li>
  <li>A variable name cannot start with a number.</li>
  <li>A variable name can only contain alpha-numeric characters and underscores (A-z, 0-9, and _ )</li>
  <li>Variable names are case-sensitive (age, Age and AGE are three different variables)</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="declarations-of-variables-using-types">Declarations of variables using types:</h3>

<pre><code class="language-python3">x = str(3)    # x will be '3'
y = int(3)    # y will be 3
z = float(3)  # z will be 3.0
</code></pre>

<pre><code class="language-python3">&gt;&gt;&gt; x = 5
&gt;&gt;&gt; y = "John"
&gt;&gt;&gt; z = 6.6
&gt;&gt;&gt; print(type(x))
&lt;class 'int'&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; print(type(y))
&lt;class 'str'&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; print(type(z))
&lt;class 'str'&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; 
</code></pre>
